## 3. Skill Verification (Proof Score)

**File:** `src/lib/analysis.ts`

### Categories

| Category | Definition | Score |
|----------|------------|-------|
| **Proven** | Skill IS a GitHub language | 100 points |
| **Inferred** | Framework maps to detected language | 50-70 points |
| **Unverified** | No GitHub evidence | 0 points |

### Scoring by Evidence Type

| Evidence Type | Points |
|---------------|--------|
| Direct Language Match | 100 |
| Strong Framework Inference | 70 |
| Tool/Partial Inference | 50 |
| No Match | 0 |

### Direct Languages (100 points)

```
python, javascript, typescript, java, c++, c#, c, go, rust, ruby, 
php, swift, kotlin, scala, r, dart, html, css, sql, shell, bash, powershell
```

### Framework → Language Mappings (70 points)

| Framework | Required Languages |
|-----------|-------------------|
| React, Vue, Angular, Next.js | JavaScript OR TypeScript |
| Django, Flask, FastAPI, Pandas | Python |
| Spring, Hibernate | Java OR Kotlin |
| ASP.NET, Unity, Blazor | C# |
| Flutter | Dart |
| Rails | Ruby |
| Laravel, Symfony | PHP |

### Tool Mappings (50 points - Partial Proof)

| Tool | Accepted Proxy Languages |
|------|-------------------------|
| Docker | Dockerfile, Shell, Python, Go |
| Kubernetes | YAML, Go, Python |
| AWS/Azure/GCP | Python, JavaScript, Go |
| MongoDB/PostgreSQL | JavaScript, Python |

### Proof Score Formula

```javascript
proofScore = average(scorePerSkill)
           = Σ(skillScore) / totalSkillCount
```

